CatDescriptText: Arnett Carter, Butcher, Centre Avenue Thorofare Market,1907 Funston Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 26, 1958, pg. 6 with question: "Do you believe the trouble in Middle East will start an atomic world war?" answer reads: "No, I don't think so."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Arnett Carter, wearing moustache, geometrically patterned short sleeve shirt, and light colored apron, standing in interior, possibly Thorofare Market, with light colored walls, and meat hook with barrel underneath on right
